 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Spatial data collection</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The GIS data which was employed as part of the CRVA in Nicaragua, Uganda and Vietnam is organized by scale from global to sub-national and displays for each component of vulnerability; selected variables, a brief description of how the data can be interpreted, the source and the spatial resolution (
  <a rid="pone.0213641.t002" ref-type="table" href="#pone.0213641.t002">Table 2</a>). The strength of this approach was to collect mainly free and open source data at the finest spatial resolution possible with the restriction to cover the full country extent.
 </p>
